This paper deals with online learning for Markov decision processes (MDPs) with stochastic long-term budget constraints, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving this problem, which involves optimization and reinforcement learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggest the possibility of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as potential sub-categories.
